      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHIMA SAND (1) missed the frame last time but prior to that was an effortless Grade 5 winner (25.01) at Ballarat, scoring by 3.5 lengths. Has the ability and can return to winning form this time. KIWI HENRY (5) lines up chasing another win after scoring over 460m at Geelong in 25.98, set up by a fast early sectional. Has won two of two starts from this draw. Can make it back-to-back wins. PAW GREGSON (2) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 3.5 lengths at Sale in a handy 28.69 beating Jumbuk Bayeh. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to his name from seven starts. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. CORA MAC (8) looks an each-way chance.",
